This product is a Git desktop client, not a general IDE.

Product priorities:
- repository status
- stage/unstage
- commit flow
- branch switching
- history graph
- diff viewer
- AI-assisted commit/review/explanation

Rules:
- Do not add full editor/IDE behavior unless explicitly requested.
- Do not introduce PR management, issue tracking, or code-generation features outside current scope.
- Keep Git flows safe and explicit.
- Preserve user changes by default.
- Warn before destructive operations.
- Treat conflicted states as first-class UX cases.
- Refresh only the necessary parts of the UI after operations.
- Prefer minimal Git commands with predictable output.

When implementing Git features:
- define the user flow first
- include preconditions and edge cases
- model staged, unstaged, untracked, conflicted states explicitly
- support binary-file and rename cases in diff/history flows